04-02-2025:

Create element by using react
ReactDOM.createRoot()
.render() -method is used to display element


HTML CODE:


<!DOCTYPE html>
<html lang="en">
<head>
    <meta charset="UTF-8">
    <meta name="viewport" content="width=device-width, initial-scale=1.0">
    <title>Document</title>
    <script crossorigin src="https://unpkg.com/react@18/umd/react.production.min.js"></script>
<script crossorigin src="https://unpkg.com/react-dom@18/umd/react-dom.production.min.js"></script>
</head>
<body>
    <div id="root"> </div>
    <script src="a.js"></script>
    <!-- link with js file -->
</body>
</html>



JAVA SCRIPT  CODE:

const b=React.createElement(
    'h1',{id:'a'}, "I am Dhanush reddy"
);

const element=document.getElementById('root')
const root=ReactDOM.createRoot(element)
root.render(b)


JSX: 
JAVASCRIPT XML:
---It is a syntax extension for js
---here we write the html code and this will be translated into js
---Babel   -tool

Points:
<br/>
<img/>
Class =className 

Code:

<script crossorigin src="https://unpkg.com/react@18/umd/react.production.min.js"></script>
    <script crossorigin src="https://unpkg.com/react-dom@18/umd/react-dom.production.min.js"></script>
    <script src="https://unpkg.com/@babel/standalone/babel.min.js"></script>
</head>
<body>
    <div id="app"> </div>
    <script type="text/babel">
        const element=<h1 className='a'>Hello JSX!</h1>
        const e=document.getElementById('app')
        const root=ReactDOM.createRoot(e)
        root.render(element)
    </script>
</body>
</html>

Expressions Inn JSX: { }
<script crossorigin src="https://unpkg.com/react@18/umd/react.production.min.js"></script>
    <script crossorigin src="https://unpkg.com/react-dom@18/umd/react-dom.production.min.js"></script>
    <script src="https://unpkg.com/@babel/standalone/babel.min.js"></script>
</head>
<body>
    <div id="app"> </div>
    <script type="text/babel">
        const element=<h1 className='a'>Hello JSX!</h1>
        const e=document.getElementById('app')
        const root=ReactDOM.createRoot(e)
        root.render(element)
    </script>
</body>
</html
